    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1093"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1093">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/306e.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Consul at Hermosillo</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1093fn1">Same to American Consuls at Mazatlan, Salina Cruz,
                        Manzanillo, and Acapulco. The telegram to the Consul at Mazatlan not
                        delivered owing to interruption of telegraphic communication.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The U. S. transport <hi rend="italic">Buford</hi> sails April 28 from San
                    Francisco to get first-hand information as to conditions affecting Americans and
                    American interests along the west coast of Mexico and to provide a means for
                    bringing to the United States those Americans who wish to leave. The vessel has
                    no offensive character whatsoever, but to avoid misinterpretation among
                    thoughtless Mexicans you will exercise discretion in making the <hi
                        rend="italic">Buford’s</hi> mission known to all Americans you can reach.
                    Cooperate in every possible way with officers of the transport, especially in
                    preventing any persons not entitled to this Government’s assistance from
                    embarking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
